      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>grated garlic </strong>(not a fan of raw garlic? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>to a small bowl with the <strong>remaining dried sage</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>winter Caesar dressing</strong></p>",
